quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,When the heaven is rent asunder
  84,2,"And gives ear unto its Lord, and is dutiful"
  84,3,And when the earth is stretched out
  84,4,"And casts forth what is within it, and is emptied (or clean)"
  84,5,"And gives ear unto its Lord, and is dutiful"
  84,6,"O man! Verily, you are toiling on towards your Lord, painfully toiling; wherefore shall you meet Him"
  84,7,And as for him who is given his record in his right hand
  84,8,His account shall be taken with an easy reckoning
  84,9,And he shall go back to his people rejoicing
  84,10,But as for him who is given his book behind his back
  84,11,He shall call out for destruction
  84,12,But he shall broil in a blazing Fire
  84,13,"Verily, he was amongst his family joyful"
  84,14,"Verily, he thought that he should never return to Allah"
  84,15,"Nay, nay! Verily, his Lord did watch him"
  84,16,So I do call as witness the glow of sunset
  84,17,"Or the night, and its homing"
  84,18,Or the moon in her fullness
  84,19,You shall surely travel from stage to stage
  84,20,What ails them that they believe not
  84,21,"And, when the Quran is read to them, they fall not prostrate"
  84,22,"On the contrary, the unbelievers reject it"
  84,23,But Allah knows best the (malice) that they hide
  84,24,So announce to them the grievous woe
  84,25,Save those who believe and work right. For them is an unfailing reward
  85,1,By the heaven with its zodiacal signs
  85,2,And by the Promised Day
  85,3,And by the witnesses and the witnessed
  85,4,Self-destroyed were the owners of the pit
  85,5,The fire of which was supplied with abundant fuel
  85,6,"Behold, they sat over it"
  85,7,And they witnessed all they were doing against the believers
  85,8,"And they mistreated them only for their belief in Allah, the Mighty, the Praiseworthy"
  85,9,Whose are the kingdoms of the heavens and the earth; for Allah is Witness over all
  85,10,"Verily, those who persecute (or mislead or tempt) the believers, men and women, and then do not repent, for them is the penalty of Hell: they will have the torment of the burning Fire"
  85,11,"Verily, those who believe and do right, for them are Gardens beneath which rivers flow: that is the great bliss"
  85,12,"Verily, strong is the power of your Lord"
  85,13,"Verily, it is He who creates and restores"
  85,14,"And He is the Forgiving, the Loving"
  85,15,The Lord of the Glorious Throne
  85,16,The Doer of what He will
  85,17,Has there come to you the story of the Hosts
  85,18,Of Pharaoh and the Thamud
  85,19,Yet the unbelievers persist in rejecting (the truth)
  85,20,But Allah is behind them - encompassing
  85,21,"Nay, this is a glorious Quran"
  85,22,(Inscribed) in a Preserved Tablet
  86,1,By the heaven and by the night or (morning) star
  86,2,And what shall make you know what the night star is
  86,3,The star of piercing brightness
  86,4,"Verily, every soul has a guardian over it"
  86,5,Then let man look from what he is created
  86,6,He is created from a drop emitted
  86,7,Which comes out from between the loins and the breast bones
  86,8,"Surely, He is able to bring back (to life)"
  86,9,On the day when the secrets shall be tried
  86,10,And man shall have neither strength nor helper
  86,11,By the Firmament which returns in its rounds
  86,12,And the earth with its sprouting
  86,13,"Verily, this is indeed a discriminating word"
  86,14,And it is no frivolity
  86,15,"As for them, they do plot a scheme"
  86,16,But I plot my scheme too
  86,17,So give respite to the unbelievers; deal you gently with them for a while